  {
    "hotel_id": "7962134",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/z-hotel/hotel/johor-bahru-my.html",
    "name": "Z HOTEL",
    "detail": "We stayed here for three nights in November. We thought the location of the hotel was excellent--close to the bus station, near the large night market, and right on the main road leading to 3 large modern malls. The bus station could be access by an overhead walkway from City Square Mall, a 5 minute walk from the hotel. The accommodations were not luxurious, but we had everything we needed and the room was clean and beds were comfortable. Two bottles of water were left for us every morning. The only downside for me was the sewer smell in the lobby. There were bags of charcoal sitting around and I also found one in my room, tucked back in a corner--I am assuming to try to combat the sewer smell, although we did not smell it in our room--only in the lobby. But the sewer smell seems to be a problem in Johor in general, and was not limited to the lobby of our hotel. All in all, we were happy with our stay here and would definitely stay again if we are ever back in Johor.",
